text: William Edward Kennedy (April 5, 1861 – December 22, 1912) was a 19th-century baseball third baseman for the Cincinnati Outlaw Reds of the Union Association in 1884. He appeared in 13 games for the Reds and hit .208. ==External links== * Category:1861 births Category:1912 deaths Category:Major League Baseball third basemen Category:Cincinnati Outlaw Reds players Category:19th-century baseball players Category:Baseball players from Kentucky
